<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C72E35FE4B0F9A3FB25F87C" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="579" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" type="description">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C72E35CE4B0F9A3FB43F992" blockId="1.[151,1437,1473,2039]" box="[199,1174,1545,1572]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C72E35CE4B0F9A3FE8CF995" bold="true" box="[199,345,1545,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Description.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="3F508B8F4C72E35CE517F9A3FE1DF995" box="[352,456,1545,1571]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Holotype</typeStatus>
female (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE65DF9A3FDB9F995" box="[554,620,1545,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1610,1634]" captionTargetBox="[268,1306,432,1550]" captionTargetId="figure-110@2.[191,1395,378,1583]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 1. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531154" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531154/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). Body length 
<quantity id="271398C84C72E35CE762F9A3FCB8F992" box="[789,877,1545,1572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" unit="mm" value="4.7">4.7 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length 
<quantity id="271398C84C72E35CE04FF9A3FB44F992" box="[1080,1169,1545,1572]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="1" pageNumber="578" unit="mm" value="3.7">3.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C72E35CE4B0F987FC97F8A9" blockId="1.[151,1437,1473,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C72E35CE4B0F987FEDBF9F1" bold="true" box="[199,270,1581,1607]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna with 26 flagellomeres; first flagellomere 1.3× longer than second flagellomere. Face (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE148F987FA41F9F1" box="[1343,1428,1581,1607]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) granulose. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE509F9FBFE07F9DD" box="[382,466,1617,1643]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2E</figureCitation>
) granulose, weakly convex in lateral view, apical margin slightly arched, sharp. Malar space granulose, its length 0.3× basal width of mandible. Mandible with a strong lamella, upper tooth slightly longer than lower tooth. Frons granulose, median carina absent. Vertex granulose. Inner margin of eye slightly indented opposite antennal socket. Eyes convergent downward. Interocellar distance (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE076F917FB82F961" box="[1025,1111,1725,1751]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2F</figureCitation>
) 1.2× ocello-ocular distance and 2.2× distance between median and lateral ocelli. Temple granulose, not swollen behind eyes. Occipital carina evenly arched, reaching hypostomal carina at mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C72E35CE4B0F883FF35F841" blockId="1.[151,1437,1473,2039]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C72E35CE4B0F883FE99F8F5" bold="true" box="[199,332,1833,1859]" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum granulose dorsally, transversely striate ventrally. Mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE0E7F883FB3EF8F5" box="[1168,1259,1833,1859]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2G</figureCitation>
), scutellum and metanotum granulose. Mesopleuron (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE633F8E7FD48F8D1" box="[580,669,1869,1895]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) granulose, weakly transversely striate below tegula. Metapleuron (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE4D7F8DBFF2FF83D" box="[160,250,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2B</figureCitation>
) granulose. Propodeum (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C72E35CE653F8DBFDAAF83D" box="[548,639,1905,1931]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="578">Fig. 2C</figureCitation>
) with area basalis triangular; area superomedia confluent with area petiolaris, slightly concave, granulose; area externa and area dentipara granulose; lateral longitudinal carina absent; lateromedian longitudinal carina and anterior transverse carina distinctly developed; propodeal spiracle nearly round.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4B0FF3CFDFAFEAB" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4B0FF3CFEDAFF06" bold="true" box="[199,271,150,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Wing.</emphasis>
Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C71E35FE5D7FF3DFE2EFF07" box="[416,507,151,177]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Fig. 2A</figureCitation>
) areolet present emitting vein 2m-cu from its apical half, with a moderate stalk. Marginal cell short, distal part of surrounding vein 2.4× longer than proximal one. Vein 1cu-a opposite M&amp;RS, 1cu-a strongly oblique, angle with vein AA 55°. External angles of second discal cell acute (70°). Hind wing with CU&amp;cu-a inclivous, not intercepted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4B0FE8DFDE8FED3" blockId="2.[151,1437,150,357]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4B0FE8DFED3FEF7" bold="true" box="[199,262,295,321]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur 4.3× longer than wide. First tarsal segment without ventral row of setae medially. Tarsal claws short, weakly pectinate basally.
</paragraph>
<caption id="B49465A54C71E35FE4E0F9E0FCAEF9D4" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531154" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6531154" box="[151,891,1610,1634]" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531154/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" startId="2.[151,250,1610,1634]" targetBox="[268,1306,432,1550]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4E0F9E0FCAEF9D4" blockId="2.[151,891,1610,1634]" box="[151,891,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4E0F9E0FEC6F9D4" bold="true" box="[151,275,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">FIGURE 1.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C71E35FE56EF9E0FDC5F9D4" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[281,528,1610,1634]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Picacharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE56EF9E0FDC5F9D4" box="[281,528,1610,1634]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Picacharops granulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE661F9E0FDB3F9D4" bold="true" box="[534,614,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C9AC54444C71E35FE661F9E0FDB3F9D4" box="[534,614,1610,1634]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, female, habitus.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4B0F93BFEBEF8E9" blockId="2.[151,1436,1680,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4B0F93BFE9EF91D" bold="true" box="[199,331,1681,1707]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Metasoma.</emphasis>
First metasomal segment (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C71E35FE6E7F93AFD38F91D" box="[656,749,1680,1707]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Fig. 2D</figureCitation>
) without glymma. First tergite 2.6× longer than width of postpetiole. Postpetiole granulose. Second tergite 0.6× as long as first tergite, slightly shorter than its apical width; thyridium circular, its distance from basal margin of tergite 0.8× its diameter. Metasoma from second tergite largely granulose and mat. Third tergite 0.6× longer than its apical width. Sixth and seventh tergites without medial emargination. Ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="78D029A84C71E35FE5B7F88AFDC2F88D" box="[448,535,1824,1851]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" captionTargetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[177,1409,181,1888]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 2. Picacharops granulosus sp. nov., holotype, female. A fore wing B mesosoma, lateral view C propodeum D first metasomal segment, lateral view E head, anterior view F head, dorsal view G mesoscutum, dorsal view H ovipositor and its sheath." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Fig. 2H</figureCitation>
) short and straight, with a distinct dorsal subapical notch, not projecting beyond apex of metasoma.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4B0F8C2FB25F87C" blockId="2.[151,1436,1680,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4B0F8C2FEF5F834" bold="true" box="[199,288,1896,1922]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Colour.</emphasis>
Black. Mandible except teeth, scape and pedicel, palpi, tegula, fore and mid legs, hind trochanter, trochantellus, medially of tibia, yellowish brown; hind coxa and femur, blackish-brown; hind tibia basally and apically, infuscated; metasoma blackish brown with apical 0.3 of second segment yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C71E359E4B0F87EFC6CFEAB" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="581" pageId="2" pageNumber="579" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C71E35FE4B0F87EFDF9F859" blockId="2.[151,1436,1680,2031]" box="[199,556,2004,2031]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C71E35FE4B0F87EFEB4F858" bold="true" box="[199,353,2004,2030]" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="98FC75BD4C71E35FE510F87EFE7FF858" box="[359,426,2004,2030]" name="China" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="222FFBCF4C71E35FE5CEF87EFDF5F859" box="[441,544,2004,2031]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="2" pageNumber="579">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B49465A54C70E35EE4E0F8D2FF0AF86E" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6531156" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6531156" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6531156/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" startId="3.[151,250,1912,1936]" targetBox="[177,1409,181,1888]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C70E35EE4E0F8D2FF0AF86E" blockId="3.[151,1436,1912,2008]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE4E0F8D2FEC1F826" bold="true" box="[151,276,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C70E35EE56CF8D2FDC6F826" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2022" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[283,531,1912,1936]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Picacharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="granulosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE56CF8D2FDC6F826" box="[283,531,1912,1936]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">Picacharops granulosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE66DF8D2FDBEF826" bold="true" box="[538,619,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C9AC54444C70E35EE66DF8D2FDBEF826" box="[538,619,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, female. 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE745F8D2FC91F826" bold="true" box="[818,836,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">A</emphasis>
fore wing 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE7C1F8D2FC12F826" bold="true" box="[950,967,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">B</emphasis>
mesosoma, lateral view 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE0B1F8D2FB0DF826" bold="true" box="[1222,1240,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">C</emphasis>
propodeum 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE12DF8D2FAB9F826" bold="true" box="[1370,1388,1912,1936]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">D</emphasis>
first metasomal segment, lateral view 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE598F836FDD5F802" bold="true" box="[495,512,1948,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">E</emphasis>
head, anterior view 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE6A3F836FD36F802" bold="true" box="[724,739,1948,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">F</emphasis>
head, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE7DFF836FC69F802" bold="true" box="[936,956,1948,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">G</emphasis>
mesoscutum, dorsal view 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C70E35EE0B9F836FB37F802" bold="true" box="[1230,1250,1948,1972]" pageId="3" pageNumber="580">H</emphasis>
ovipositor and its sheath.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0FF3DFC6CFEAB" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0FF3DFEC4FF07" bold="true" box="[199,273,151,177]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Notes.</emphasis>
The distribution of the two known species of 
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C77E359E753FF3DFC65FF07" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1984" box="[804,944,151,177]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Picacharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E753FF3DFC65FF07" box="[804,944,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Picacharops</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely disjunct, 
<collectingCountry id="98FC75BD4C77E359E0E5FF3DFB00FF07" box="[1170,1237,151,177]" name="China" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="98FC75BD4C77E359E17AFF3DFAA2FF07" box="[1293,1399,151,177]" name="Australia" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Australia</collectingCountry>
, so until further specimens are able to be examined, we have placed this new species in this 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E0F8FF11FAC4FF63" box="[1167,1297,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Picacharop</emphasis>
because the new species matches the generic characters well. This new species, however, differs distinctly from the only other known species of this genus, 
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E5A8FEA9FD56FEAB" box="[479,643,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<taxonomicName id="27EB4EAE4C77E359E5A8FEA9FDAAFEAB" authorityName="Gauld" authorityYear="1984" box="[479,639,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Picacharops" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevithorax">P. brevithorax</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
as shown in the key above.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8F166A64C77E359E4B0FE8DFED9FED3" pageId="4" pageNumber="581" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E054352D4C77E359E4B0FE8DFED9FED3" blockId="4.[151,1437,151,357]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">
<emphasis id="D29FE93F4C77E359E4B0FE8DFE9BFEF7" bold="true" box="[199,334,295,321]" pageId="4" pageNumber="581">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from “granosus” (Latin for “granular”), because its body sculpture is largely granulose.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
